	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 10th 10:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>With my hafling rogue, I am a master thief. He is only level 5 right now, but this is th reason I call him the "master thief". One day I was bored, so I logged onto my hafling rogue &lt;Rallos Zek server&gt; and just began sneaking and hiding, and decided to walk around town like that. Well I came upon 2 people, and they appeared to be trading, they were saying stuff like, 2500pp? Deal. Well I decided to stick around just to see what was going on, and then when they were trading, the one person apparently didn't have enough room in their inventory, and the backpack containing all of the items, fell to the ground. Well guess who picked it up! Me! I grabbed the bag, and then they started saying things like: Where did it go? And became worried, looking around, and shouting out messages about a lost bag. Well no way was I giving it back! I looked inside and there was so much good stuff! I had in it: 2 shadowbone earrings, 2 ebony bladed swords, a bloodstained tunic, lizardscale mantle, a 8 dose SOW potion, and Blackened Alloy Bastard Sword! All this stuff rocks! The only problem was, later on, I went Ld, and when I logged back on the next day, everything I had was gone! Verant said they weren't resbonsible for me going Ld, and they said that I shouldn't be giving newer characters items like that. I told them that I stole them, and they said I deserved it anyways then. I just told them: I'm a rogue! Sue me! And they left. I really wanted all that stuff, but I can live without it! I still have the beautiful satisfaction of being the well known thief in my area! Great tale to tell too!<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
